From 626200df2498ff3044170d0f02b463ac0ec899c5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Rander Wang <rander.wang@intel.com>
Date: Fri, 21 Aug 2020 14:55:58 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] SoC: Intel: sof_sdw: Add support for product Ripto
References: jsc#SLE-16518
Patch-mainline: Queued in subsystem maintainer repository
Git-repo: git://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/broonie/sound.git
Git-commit: 626200df2498ff3044170d0f02b463ac0ec899c5

Ripto is another product based on TGL with the same
audio hardware configuration as Volteer.

Reviewed-by: Bard Liao <yung-chuan.liao@linux.intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Rander Wang <rander.wang@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Pierre-Louis Bossart <pierre-louis.bossart@linux.intel.com>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20200821195603.215535-12-pierre-louis.bossart@linux.intel.com
Signed-off-by: Mark Brown <broonie@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 sound/soc/intel/boards/sof_sdw.c | 9 +++++++++
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+)

diff --git a/sound/soc/intel/boards/sof_sdw.c b/sound/soc/intel/boards/sof_sdw.c
index ca231459ac10..44d06fa48b24 100644
--- a/sound/soc/intel/boards/sof_sdw.c
+++ b/sound/soc/intel/boards/sof_sdw.c
@@ -123,6 +123,15 @@ static const struct dmi_system_id sof_sdw_quirk_table[] = {
 		.driver_data = (void *)(SOF_SDW_TGL_HDMI | SOF_SDW_PCH_DMIC |
 					SOF_SDW_FOUR_SPK),
 	},
+	{
+		.callback = sof_sdw_quirk_cb,
+		.matches = {
+			DMI_MATCH(DMI_SYS_VENDOR, "Google"),
+			DMI_MATCH(DMI_PRODUCT_NAME, "Ripto"),
+		},
+		.driver_data = (void *)(SOF_SDW_TGL_HDMI | SOF_SDW_PCH_DMIC |
+					SOF_SDW_FOUR_SPK),
+	},
 
 	{}
 };
